{"id":"636","name":"Check Trade Me","tagline":"Enables Kiwis to check the prices on Trade Me for (almost) any online goods on other apps/sites","icon":"ios12 c4274264319 g59848","latest":"1343","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p><code>Check Trade Me</code> enables Kiwis to check the prices on Trade Me for (almost) any online goods available on other apps/sites.</p>\n<p>Steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Browse the web / apps as you normally do until you find a product you wish to buy</li>\n<li>Tap the Share button / Open an Activity Sheet</li>\n<li>Select Shortcuts &gt; Check Trade Me</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Just remember to <code>Check Trade Me</code> before tapping that Buy button run this shortcut via the Activity Sheet to make sure you are not spending more than you need to.</p>\n<p>If you have the Trade Me app installed it will open it, otherwise it will load the Mobile Optimised website.</p>\n<p>Please let me know if you come across any websites where this Shortcut fails. </p>\n<p>Disclosure: this is a hobby project that scratches my own itch. The shortcut was not commissioned by Trade Me.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.3 - Oct. 31, 2018, 9:12 p.m.</strong></p><p>Fixed an issue that left the Shortcut in an odd state after running in certain scenarios. </p>"}